# Exclude Windows build artifacts that contain machine-specific paths.
# Without this, Docker copies the obj/ folders from your Windows machine into
# the Linux container. Those obj/ folders contain project.assets.json files
# with Windows-only paths (e.g. C:\Program Files\...\NuGetPackages) baked in,
# which causes NuGet to crash with "Unable to find fallback package folder".
# By excluding obj/ and bin/, dotnet restore inside Docker generates fresh
# Linux-compatible paths and publish succeeds.

**/obj/
**/bin/
**/.vs/
**/*.user
**/build-log.txt
